STA36149 | Freshman Seminar: Astronomy in the Era of Big Data: Astronomy in the Era of Big Data | https://enr-apps.as.cmu.edu/open/SOC/SOCServlet/courseDetails?COURSE=36149&SEMESTER=S15 | instructors:Freeman, Peter description:Astronomy in the 21st century is a discipline that is being flooded with data. In this course, you will learn about some of the things that astronomers (and astronomically minded statisticians) wish to determine by harnessing the power of these data, such as how our Universe evolved, how many Earth-sized planets orbit nearby stars, and how often extinction-causing meteors hit the Earth, etc. You will synthesize what you learn by using it to inform opinion-editorial (Op-Ed) style articles and blog entries, as well as oral presentations. You will also be introduced to the statistical package R, which you will apply to simple analyses of astronomical data. Note that in the Level 4 multiverse, you have enjoyed taking this class an infinite number of times. Welcome back!
